Cell imaging of Human cervical carcinoma Hela cells were conducted to assess the fluorescence properties of D-GQDs [43–45]. The original cells were cultured in 50 μg/mL Dulbecco's Modified Eagle Medium (DMEM) medium, as shown in Fig. 6
                        a. After incubation at 37 °C for 24 h, the D-GQDs entered into the cells and migrated from cytoplasm towards nucleus (Fig. 6b). Three random regions of the cells were selected for imaging observation (460 nm excitation). It demonstrated that the Hela cells incubated with D-GQDs maintain their original shape and clearly exhibited green fluorescence for all the three regions (Fig. 6c), suggesting its pronounced fluorescence properties of D-GQDs. More importantly, when the volume of D-GQDs increased from 1 to 20 μL (Fig. 7
                        ), cell viability remained almost 100%. These results suggest the D-GQDs exhibited good biocompatibility and low cytotoxicity in biomedical imaging.
